<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="15" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,152,1222]" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,515,770,796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
:—Epiphytic on trees in the interior of the mountain forest along the Rio Urubamba, 
<collectingRegion box="[289,365,809,835]" country="Peru" name="Cusco" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Cusco</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[377,431,809,835]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Peru</collectingCountry>
at an elevation of about 
<quantity box="[720,812,809,835]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.07" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" unit="m" value="2070.0">2070 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,152,1222]" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,327,847,873]" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Etimology</emphasis>
:—This 
<taxonomicName box="[425,545,848,873]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[425,545,848,873]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Guzmania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named in honour of the Inkaterra organisation of Machu Picchu Pueblo Hotel, its owner José Koechlin and the head of the gardens Carmen Soto, who are very enthusiastic about the native plants, the biodiversity and the environment of that area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,152,1222]" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,364,963,989]" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Observations</emphasis>
:—This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Mez (1896: 932)" authorityName="Mez" authorityPageNumber="932" authorityYear="1896" box="[756,1247,964,990]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="morreniana">
<emphasis box="[756,1026,964,989]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Guzmania morreniana</emphasis>
Mez (1896: 932)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(H. Luther) Betancur &amp; Salinas (2003: 23)" authorityName="Betancur &amp; Salinas" authorityPageNumber="23" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="H. Luther" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">Guzmania tenuifolia</emphasis>
(H.Luther) Betancur &amp; Salinas (2003: 23)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from them by its larger size and flower parts. The plant is flowering about 
<quantity box="[497,586,1041,1067]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" unit="cm" value="130.0">130 cm</quantity>
tall (vs. 
<quantity box="[692,766,1041,1067]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" unit="cm" value="60.0">60 cm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Betancur &amp; Salinas" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="H. Luther" box="[805,951,1041,1066]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Guzmania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="5" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuifolia">
<emphasis box="[805,951,1041,1066]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="15">G. tenuifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
